                  "value": {
                    "_type": "DV_TEXT",
                    "value": "Due to an intermediate–high risk profile, the patient was initially admitted to and monitored in the intermediate care unit (IMC). Acute treatment was initiated immediately with intravenous anticoagulation using unfractionated heparin (UFH), along with oxygen administration via nasal cannula. Under the initiated therapy, rapid hemodynamic stabilization was observed, accompanied by declining cardiac biomarkers. The treatment was subsequently transitioned to oral anticoagulation with rivaroxaban."
